# Personal /teach workspace state — generated per-user, not template content.
# Contains personal progress, assessments and machine-specific paths; the repo
# is public, so keep it out of version control. Each user generates their own.
/MISSION.md
/NOTES.md
/learning-records/

# Rendered lessons: generated during /teach sessions with real project data
# (paths, model names). The shared .md briefs and assets/lesson.css ARE tracked.
/lessons/*.html

# Lesson lifecycle gate: agent-written progress state mirrored into index.html.
# Per-user progress; the tracker UI (index.html) IS tracked. See ADR-0004.
/progress.json

# Per-user lesson setup (reference project, language, pedagogy). The schema
# reference learning-config.example.md IS tracked. See ADR-0001.
/learning-config.md
